Jurgen Klopp has stated that the club are looking to hold on to their star players, with rumours having it that Mane, Firmino and Salah are to be offered new contracts. Liverpool lost star midfielder, Philippe Coutinho to Barcelona in the January transfer window and are keen on holding to their current stars. Sadio Mane has attracted interest from top European clubs, and Salah is being courted by Real Madrid. And Firmino is earning praise from every corner of Europe. Quizzed on a possible contract extension for Mane, who is already tied to Liverpool until 2021, the Reds boss said: “There’s nothing to do about that. “That we want to keep the players together is not a secret. “We want to keep Sadio here – keep this team and strengthen it. It’s completely normal.” The post Klopp: Liverpool Hoping To Keep Mane appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.